"title": "1230: God, the Lord",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1230: god, the lord",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God is the almighty ruler to whom everything and everyone is subject. His lordship is seen in his power and his victory over his enemies and also in his deliverance of his people and his loving care for them. He is the recipient of their obedience and their prayers. (“Lord” is the translation of the Hebrew word “Adonai” meaning “Ruler” or “Master” and is distinct from “LORD” which is the translation of the divine name “Yahweh”.).</p>\n<h2>God is the almighty ruler</h2>\n<h3>He is Lord of lords</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:15\">1TI 6:15</a></strong> <em>God exercises his lordship over all creation, but especially over all humanity.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:17\">DEU 10:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps136:3\">PSA 136:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:47\">DAN 2:47</a></p>\n<h3>He is Lord of all the earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:5\">PSA 97:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:11\">JOS 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:13\">JOS 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:13\">MIC 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:14\">ZEC 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24\">ACT 17:24</a></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of God as Lord</h2>\n<h3>He is great and powerful</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:5\">PSA 147:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:14\">NEH 4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:8\">PSA 86:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps114:7-Ps114:8\">PSA 114:7–114:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:5\">PSA 135:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:2\">ISA 28:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:4\">DAN 9:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:24\">ACT 4:24</a></p>\n<h3>He is majestic and exalted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1\">ISA 6:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:1\">PSA 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps8:9\">PSA 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:9\">2TH 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>He is righteous</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:16\">DAN 9:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:5-Ps97:6\">PSA 97:5–97:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:7\">DAN 9:7</a></p>\n<h3>He is loving and caring</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:15\">PSA 86:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:12\">PSA 62:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:5\">PSA 86:5</a></p>\n<h3>He is merciful and forgiving</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:9\">DAN 9:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:3-Ps86:5\">PSA 86:3–86:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:2-Ps130:4\">PSA 130:2–130:4</a></p>\n<h2>God, the Lord, is triumphant over his enemies</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:65-Ps78:66\">PSA 78:65–78:66</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:4-Ps2:5\">PSA 2:4–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:13\">PSA 37:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:5-Ps110:6\">PSA 110:5–110:6</a></p>\n<h2>God, the Lord, delivers his people and cares for them</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:19\">PSA 68:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:15\">PSA 38:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:22\">PSA 38:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:17\">PSA 40:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps54:4\">PSA 54:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:11\">PSA 59:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:2\">PSA 77:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:1\">PSA 90:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:17\">PSA 90:17</a></p>\n<h2>God is addressed as Lord</h2>\n<h3>As a mark of respect or obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:14\">JOS 5:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:10\">EXO 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:13\">EXO 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:22\">EXO 5:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:15\">JDG 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:29\">LUK 2:29</a></p>\n<h3>In prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:11\">NEH 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:27\">GEN 18:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:30-Gen18:32\">GEN 18:30–18:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:9\">EXO 34:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:8\">JOS 7:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:8\">JDG 13:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:8\">PSA 30:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:4\">DAN 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:15\">DAN 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:19\">DAN 9:19</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is God, the Lord</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:28\">JHN 20:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:41-Matt22:45\">MAT 22:41–22:45</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:35-Mark12:37\">MRK 12:35–12:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:41-Luke20:44\">LUK 20:41–20:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:34-Acts2:36\">ACT 2:34–2:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:13\">HEB 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a></p>",
